  "extras": {
    "summary": "A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION APPLYING TO THE UNITED STATES  CONGRESS TO CALL A CONVENTION OF THE STATES UNDER THE PROVISIONS  OF ARTICLE V OF THE CONSTITUTION OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE  PURPOSE OF PROPOSING AN AMENDMENT TO THE CONSTITUTION TO SET A LIMIT ON THE NUMBER OF TERMS THAT A PERSON MAY BE ELECTED AS A MEMBER OF THE UNITED STATES HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES AND TO SET A LIMIT ON THE NUMBER OF TERMS THAT A PERSON MAY BE ELECTED AS A MEMBER OF THE UNITED STATES SENATE."
